<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tyler</persName> to <gloss type="to">acting British consul-general</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-18"><hi rend="italic">April 18,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 7.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Do whatever is necessary on behalf of Bagdasarian; legation will support
                            you. I have again insisted on his release. Don’t allow any money
                            payment.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>